{{Orphan|date=February 2017}}

'''Kim Goodman''' is a woman who is able to pop her [[human eye|eye]]s out of her eye sockets by 12 millimeters (0.47&nbsp;inches).<ref name="Melissa2009">{{cite book|last=Melissa|first=Stewart,|title=The Eyes Have it: The Secrets of Eyes and Seeing|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QVTqnAist2MC&pg=PA19|accessdate=6 April 2013|date=2009-09-01|publisher=Marshall Cavendish|isbn=9780761445944|pages=19–}}</ref><ref name="Glenday2010">{{cite book|last=Glenday|first=Craig|title=Guinness World Records 2010: Thousands of New Records in The Book of the Decade!|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=rZ8nFo7Ep0AC&pg=PA97|accessdate=6 April 2013|date=2010-04-27|publisher=Random House Digital, Inc.|isbn=9780553593372|pages=97–}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=IjBZAAAAIBAJ&sjid=gUcNAAAAIBAJ&pg=5461,2193064&dq=kim+goodman+eyeball&hl=en|title=Eye-popping Feats Rated .|date=November 16, 2004|work=The Union Democrat|accessdate=6 April 2013}}</ref> She holds the [[world record]] for the farthest eyeball protrusion. She lives in [[Chicago]], [[Illinois]]. She discovered her eyeball popping talent one day when she was hit over the head. Her eyeballs popped out much further than usual and ever since that day she could pop them out on cue, as well as when she [[Yawning|yawns]].<ref name=Glenday2010/>

She has appeared on the [[Late Show with David Letterman]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-68978269.html|title=They do what? (subscription required)|last=Carr|first=Amy|date=March 30, 1998|work=Daily Herald|accessdate=6 April 2013}}</ref><ref name=bct>{{cite news|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=MahUAAAAIBAJ&sjid=kTsNAAAAIBAJ&pg=1461,5655410&dq=kim+goodman+born+eyeball&hl=en|title='Letterman' Stunt was Eye-Popping|date=February 25, 1997|work=Beaver County Times|accessdate=6 April 2013}}</ref>

In 2004, Goodman was included by [[Guinness World Records]] in their 50th anniversary list of top ten "feats" of all time.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=VDBB&p_theme=vdbb&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=1066639306DBD72B&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM|title=Guinness names top 10 feats|date=November 16, 2004|work=Inland Valley Daily Bulletin|accessdate=6 April 2013}}</ref>

