The '''Pacific Coast Association of Magicians''' is an American association of [[illusionist]]s. It was founded in 1933;{{r|bc}} the first president was [[Lloyd Jones (magician)|Lloyd E Jones]].{{cn|date=August 2018}} It has chapters in [[Japan]], [[Hawaii]], [[California]], and western [[Canada]], and holds an annual convention.{{r|bc}} The third of these, in 1935, was held at the [[Knickerbocker Hotel (Los Angeles)|Knickerbocker Hotel]] in [[Hollywood]], and was attended by [[Bess Houdini]], widow of [[Harry Houdini]].{{r|kcet}} In 2018 the convention was held in [[Bakersfield, California]].{{r|bc|bn}}
From September 1936 to August 1937 the magazine ''[[Genii (magazine)|Genii]]'', published by William W. Larsen, was the official organ of the association.<ref>https://www.lybrary.com/genii-volume-01-p-461190.html</ref>
